<TOOL_PURPOSE>
The Think Tool is a strategic reasoning mechanism for complex problem-solving, providing a transparent log of analytical thought processes.
Key Objectives:

Facilitate deep reasoning without repository modifications
Log thought processes for clarity and transparency
Support strategic decision-making across various scenarios
</TOOL_PURPOSE>

<USE_CASES>

Repository Bug Resolution


Brainstorm multiple bug-fixing approaches
Assess complexity and effectiveness of potential solutions
Evaluate simplest and most impactful fixes


Test Failure Analysis


Explore potential causes of test failures
Generate hypothetical resolution strategies
Systematically evaluate debugging approaches


Refactoring Planning


Outline different refactoring approaches
Analyze trade-offs of potential implementation strategies
Identify most efficient refactoring method


Feature Design


Explore architectural possibilities
Evaluate implementation details
Consider potential challenges and solutions


Complex Issue Debugging


Organize hypotheses and reasoning
Systematically break down complex problems
Create structured approach to troubleshooting
</USE_CASES>

<CORE_CHARACTERISTICS>

Purely analytical tool
Does not execute code
Does not modify repository
Focuses on logging thought process
Enhances problem-solving transparency
</CORE_CHARACTERISTICS>

<PARAMETERS>
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "thought": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Detailed reasoning or brainstorming log"
    }
  },
  "required": ["thought"]
}
</PARAMETERS>
<COMMAND>
Default command set to empty string to satisfy artifact requirements.

</COMMAND>

<MANDATORY_USAGE>
The 'think' tool MUST be used before any non-trivial, multi-step, or ambiguous action. This is required for all workflows and is enforced by the core.mdc rules. Use this tool to ensure deep reasoning, optimal methodology, and to avoid quick fixes or temporary solutions.
</MANDATORY_USAGE>